items.name: cast
items.desc: Converts any type of variable to a string.

items.name: changeCase
items.desc: Converts the case of a string.

items.name: escapeAllQuotes
items.desc: Escapes all quotes (single and double) from a given string.

items.name: escapeDquotes
items.desc: Escapes the string in double quotes.

items.name: escapeDquote
items.desc: Synonym of "escape_dquotes".

items.name: escapeQuote
items.desc: Synonym of "escape_dquotes".

items.name: escapeQuotes
items.desc: Synonym of "escape_dquotes".

items.name: escapeSquotes
items.desc: Escapes the string in quotes.

items.name: unescapeSquotes
items.desc: Unescapes the string in quotes.

items.name: unescapeSquote
items.desc: Unescapes the string in quotes.

items.name: escape
items.desc: Synonym of "escape_squotes".

items.name: escapeApo
items.desc: Synonym of "escape_squotes".

items.name: escapeSquote
items.desc: Synonym of "escape_squotes".

items.name: clean
items.desc: Returns an expunged string of several types of character(s) depending on the configuration.

items.name: cut
items.desc: Cuts a string (HTML and PHP tags stripped) to maximum length inserted.

items.name: encodeFilename
items.desc: Returns a cross-platform filename for the file.

items.name: encodeDbname
items.desc: Returns a corrected string for database naming.

items.name: fileExt
items.desc: Returns the file extension.

items.name: genpwd
items.desc: Returns a random password.

items.name: isJson
items.desc: Checks if the string is a json string.

items.name: isNumber
items.desc: Checks if the item is a number.

items.name: isInteger
items.desc: Checks if the item is a integer.

items.name: isCleanPath
items.desc: Checks if ".. \\" or "../" is contained in the parameter and it will return false if true.

items.name: isDecimal
items.desc: Checks if the item is a decimal.

items.name: isUid
items.desc: Checks if the string is a valid UID string.

items.name: isBuid
items.desc: Checks if the string is a valid binary UID string.

items.name: isEmail
items.desc: Checks if the string is the correct type of e-mail address.

items.name: isUrl
items.desc: Checks if the argument is a valid URL string.

items.name: isDomain
items.desc: Checks if the argument is a valid domain name.

items.name: isDateSql
items.desc: Checks if the argument is in a valid SQL date format.

items.name: correctTypes
items.desc: If it looks like an int or float type, the string variable is converted into the correct type.

items.name: parseUrl
items.desc: Returns an array containing any of the various components of the URL that are present.

items.name: parsePath
items.desc: Replaces backslash with slash in a path string. Forbids the use of ../

items.name: removeAccents
items.desc: Replaces accented characters with their character without the accent.

items.name: checkName
items.desc: Checks if a string complies with SQL naming convention.

items.name: checkFilename
items.desc: Checks if a string doesn't contain a filesystem path.

items.name: checkPath
items.desc: Checks if a string doesn't contain a filesystem path.

items.name: hasSlash
items.desc: Checks if a string complies with SQL naming convention.

items.name: getNumbers
items.desc: Extracts all digits from a string.

items.name: makeReadable
items.desc: Returns the argumented value, replacing not standard objects (not stdClass) by their class name.

items.name: export
items.desc: Returns a variable in a mode that is directly usable by PHP.

items.name: replaceOnce
items.desc: Replaces part of a string. If the part is not found, the method returns the string without change.

items.name: removeComments
items.desc: Removes the comments.

items.name: saySize
items.desc: Converts the bytes to another unit form.

items.name: checkJson
items.desc: Checks whether a JSON string is valid or not. If $return_error is set to true, the error will be returned.

items.name: markdown2html
items.desc: Transforms a markdown string into HTML.

items.name: toCamel
items.desc: Converts the given string to camel case.

items.name: html2text
items.desc: Converts HTML to text replacing paragraphs and brs with new lines.

items.name: text2html
items.desc: Converts text to HTML replacing new lines with brs.
